- 'Morning.
- 'Morning.

01:47.899 --> 01:49.300
'Morning.

02:04.965 --> 02:07.986
'Morning.

02:38.075 --> 02:41.646
'Morning.

02:41.746 --> 02:43.805
'Morning.

03:12.693 --> 03:14.303
Gentlemen, let's go to work!

03:14.403 --> 03:15.404
Pritchard.

03:16.071 --> 03:19.016
How are we doing
with our development in Brazil?

03:19.116 --> 03:24.771
Mr. Bolt, we just learned that in order
to build Club Bolt the way you envision,

03:24.871 --> 03:29.627
we'd be forced to cut down 6,000 acres
of natural Brazilian rain forest.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.174
So?

03:32.504 --> 03:37.726
Sir, the last 400 remaining Ipi Indians
left in the world are still living there.

03:39.094 --> 03:40.141
So?

03:41.972 --> 03:45.250
Sir, if we cut down their forest,

03:45.350 --> 03:49.355
we'd have to displace them,
and they could cause trouble.

03:51.481 --> 03:54.092
Well, they're not gonna
want to live there anymore anyway.

03:54.192 --> 03:55.239
Why not?

03:55.527 --> 03:56.528
No shade.

03:59.781 --> 04:02.034
How are we doing with
our new development in Florida?

04:03.160 --> 04:07.165
Well, sir, we are having
a slight problem in Fort Lauderdale.

04:07.330 --> 04:12.177
In order to make room for the magnificent,
largest-in-the-world Bolt shopping mall,

04:12.294 --> 04:15.173
we're going to have to
tear down a nursing home for the aged.

04:15.672 --> 04:16.673
So?

04:18.216 --> 04:21.327
Well, at present, there are
180 very old people living there.

04:21.428 --> 04:25.228
And we understand that most of them
are invalids, who are bedridden and dying.

04:25.807 --> 04:26.854
So?

04:29.519 --> 04:31.146
It wouldn't look good in the papers.

04:31.438 --> 04:33.816
I get your point.

04:36.234 --> 04:37.861
Do it late at night.

04:38.779 --> 04:39.826
Excellent!

04:43.867 --> 04:46.416
Gentlemen, I have a little surprise.

04:47.788 --> 04:48.772
Follow me.

04:48.872 --> 04:50.857
- What is this?
- It looks like a slum area.

04:50.957 --> 04:53.193
You are looking at
two-and-a-half square miles

04:53.293 --> 04:56.947
of the most derelict,
dilapidated section of Los Angeles.

04:57.047 --> 04:59.574
Right now, I own half of this property.

04:59.674 --> 05:01.201
The city owns the other half.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.555
But by noon tomorrow,
it will all be mine.

05:05.806 --> 05:06.898
What is that?

05:07.390 --> 05:09.893
One of those little bums
that live down there.

05:12.562 --> 05:14.297
I suppose you're wondering
why Goddard Bolt

05:14.397 --> 05:18.969
is prepared to pay up to $4 billion
to own this worthless pile of refuse.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.138
Am I right?

05:21.238 --> 05:25.809
Well, we would never presume to question
your genius for financial wizardry, sir.

05:25.909 --> 05:27.126
But why?

05:28.745 --> 05:30.213
Wait.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.872
Gentlemen,
the ultimate achievement of my life!

05:46.972 --> 05:48.206
Bolt Center!

05:48.306 --> 05:49.499
It's absolutely visionary!

05:49.599 --> 05:50.584
Fantastic!

05:50.684 --> 05:52.085
Incredible!

05:52.185 --> 05:56.440
Gentlemen, you'll never know
how much this project excites me!

06:01.987 --> 06:03.847
Mr. Bolt, you have a surprise visitor.

06:03.947 --> 06:05.915
- Who is it?
- Vance Crasswell, sir.

06:06.157 --> 06:07.704
Crasswell! Damn it!

06:12.622 --> 06:14.374
Thank you. Let's go.

06:16.084 --> 06:19.304
Excuse me. Am I interrupting?

06:20.505 --> 06:22.032
I'm interrupting.

06:22.132 --> 06:23.867
I'm interrupting. I should leave.

06:23.967 --> 06:26.311
Should I leave? I'm gonna leave.

06:28.013 --> 06:29.105
Can I come in?

06:29.264 --> 06:30.265
Hello, Vance.

06:30.807 --> 06:33.043
You know my attorneys,
Pritchard, Knowles, Stevens.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.771
The three wise men. Hiya, fellas.

06:36.146 --> 06:37.380
What's goin' on?

06:37.480 --> 06:38.857
Oh, my God!

06:39.482 --> 06:40.859
Oh, my God!

06:41.234 --> 06:45.159
Someone else's idea of what to do
with the Downtown slum district.

06:45.530 --> 06:46.656
Would you...

06:48.158 --> 06:50.185
Why didn't they tell me
Goddard Bolt owned the other half?

06:50.285 --> 06:52.333
I never would've bought it.

06:52.662 --> 06:56.399
No one beats Goddard Bolt when it comes
to financial wheeling and dealing.

06:56.499 --> 07:00.195
Now, look. I'm in way over my head here.

07:00.295 --> 07:03.799
I'm sorry to have wasted your time,
gentlemen.

07:06.843 --> 07:08.015
Mr. Bolt.

07:08.887 --> 07:10.139
Can I ask you a question?

07:10.805 --> 07:12.022
Let me buy your half of the property.

07:13.224 --> 07:15.961
Give you $2 billion,
4% of the profit for the next 20 years.

07:16.061 --> 07:17.128
No.

07:17.228 --> 07:18.821
- 5%.
- No.

07:19.356 --> 07:20.983
- 6%.
- Stop.

07:21.274 --> 07:22.366
Stopped.

07:22.859 --> 07:26.079
Vance, why don't you let me buy you out?

07:26.321 --> 07:27.368
Look at us.

07:27.697 --> 07:30.291
An office is no place to do business.

07:32.243 --> 07:33.711
I have a much better idea.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.717
Now, isn't this better?

07:39.209 --> 07:41.528
At least we can see
what we're dealing with.

07:41.628 --> 07:43.801
Okay. Final offer.

07:46.967 --> 07:48.969
I want this property.

07:49.386 --> 07:50.512
I want it.

07:51.721 --> 07:55.771
Just so happens I grew up
five blocks from where we're standing.

07:57.394 --> 07:58.896
I'm all right.

08:00.522 --> 08:03.492
Right in the middle
of this godforsaken slum.

08:04.150 --> 08:07.950
It's been my life-long dream
to come back here and rebuild it.

08:09.572 --> 08:11.141
It's okay. You can laugh.

08:11.241 --> 08:12.934
I don't expect you
to understand my feelings.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.911
After all, you're a rich man's son.

08:15.036 --> 08:16.813
You were born into money.

08:16.913 --> 08:18.982
What, are you kidding?
My father left me $5 million.

08:19.082 --> 08:20.150
That's nothing.

08:20.250 --> 08:22.652
No, no, no. Nothing is nothing!

08:22.752 --> 08:25.596
These people down here have nothing!
Zero!

08:26.631 --> 08:29.117
Look, I don't want
to hurt your feelings.

08:29.217 --> 08:31.470
You? You couldn't survive
10 minutes down here.

08:31.803 --> 08:32.996
Don't be ridiculous.

08:33.096 --> 08:34.938
I would survive anywhere.

08:35.097 --> 08:36.315
Right.

08:36.975 --> 08:38.568
Without your money
and your credit cards?

08:39.059 --> 08:40.169
Yes.

08:40.270 --> 08:43.590
Without identifying yourself
to anyone as Goddard Bolt?

08:43.690 --> 08:44.862
Yes.

08:45.275 --> 08:46.635
For a modest period of time.

08:46.735 --> 08:49.454
I don't know, let's say 30 days?

08:50.363 --> 08:51.455
Absolutely!

08:52.949 --> 08:54.292
It's a bet.

08:55.076 --> 08:56.123
Bet?

08:56.619 --> 08:57.996
What are you talking about?

08:58.455 --> 08:59.689
Well, what you just said.

08:59.789 --> 09:03.860
That you could survive down here without
using any of your resources for 30 days.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.987
And if you do it,
you get my half of the property.

09:06.087 --> 09:08.966
You don't do it, I'm gonna get yours.

09:10.300 --> 09:12.553
I'm sorry, wasn't that the bet?

09:17.515 --> 09:20.894
You conniving son-of-a-bitch.

09:24.022 --> 09:25.114
Yes!

09:26.566 --> 09:27.943
It's a bet.

09:28.985 --> 09:31.329
You've underestimated me, Vance.

09:31.446 --> 09:32.823
I can do it!

09:33.615 --> 09:36.243
You can't do it! You'll never make it!

09:36.618 --> 09:38.603
This is insane. This is crazy!

09:38.703 --> 09:39.896
You'll never survive!

09:39.996 --> 09:41.748
Pritchard, be quiet.

09:43.083 --> 09:44.175
- Fergueson, go on.
- Thank you.

09:44.334 --> 09:47.654
Now, if you leave the prescribed slum area
or try to remove this ankle alarm,

09:47.754 --> 09:49.051
it will go off.

09:49.214 --> 09:53.076
And if we receive a sustained alarm signal
for more than 30 seconds,

09:53.176 --> 09:54.744
you'll forfeit the bet.

09:54.844 --> 09:58.081
After 30 days, the alarm
will automatically deactivate.

09:58.181 --> 09:59.649
Are these conditions understood?

10:00.100 --> 10:01.101
Understood.

10:01.518 --> 10:02.940
And we have your word on that.

10:03.228 --> 10:05.356
Yes, you have my word on it.

10:05.980 --> 10:10.201
Pritchard, I'm giving you and your partners
my power of attorney.

10:10.360 --> 10:14.365
I'm trusting you to look after
all my legal affairs for the next 30 days.

10:17.867 --> 10:19.728
Take it. Take it all.

10:19.828 --> 10:21.455
I won't need anything.

10:22.539 --> 10:24.712
And you won't need this either.

10:28.002 --> 10:29.279
What are you doing?

10:29.379 --> 10:32.508
Have to make sure no one recognizes you.

10:32.632 --> 10:34.430
That was stitched in.

10:37.387 --> 10:38.889
Give me a comb.

10:43.893 --> 10:46.629
Mr. Bolt, I don't think you realize
what you're getting into!

10:46.729 --> 10:48.006
You've never slept in the street before.

10:48.106 --> 10:49.591
You've never eaten out of garbage cans.

10:49.691 --> 10:51.051
You're used to a hearty breakfast.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.218
This is ludicrous.

10:52.318 --> 10:53.803
Look at you without your toupee.

10:53.903 --> 10:57.307
You look like somebody
who only makes $50,000 a year.

10:57.407 --> 10:59.893
Mr. Bolt, please don't do this.

10:59.993 --> 11:02.312
Let me suggest you wait 24 hours.

11:02.412 --> 11:04.147
Yes, at least sleep on it.

11:04.247 --> 11:05.999
I've given my word.

11:06.249 --> 11:08.359
Do you want me to go back on my word?

11:08.459 --> 11:09.986
Would you go back on your word?

11:10.086 --> 11:12.088
Certainly. We're lawyers.

11:13.965 --> 11:15.842
Give me that contract.

11:26.728 --> 11:29.607
Okay, Goddard, here we are.

11:30.356 --> 11:31.608
Come on.

11:33.693 --> 11:39.015
Now, in 30 days,
at the exact moment of sunset,

11:39.115 --> 11:42.310
all of this property
is going to be yours or mine.

11:42.410 --> 11:45.129
Either way, I think we should
have a big party at my house.

11:45.955 --> 11:47.065
Let's make it at my house.

11:47.165 --> 11:48.883
Okay, your house.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.261
For the look.

11:56.799 --> 11:57.846
Thanks.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.012
Let's get out of here.

12:11.189 --> 12:14.384
It's going to be hot,
H-O-T, with a capital "H,"

12:14.484 --> 12:16.136
for at least the next few days.

12:16.236 --> 12:17.720
Do whatever you can to keep cool.

12:17.820 --> 12:19.889
And for the low tonight,
we're not going to get much relief.

12:19.989 --> 12:23.163
It's only going to get down
to maybe the high 80s.

12:25.328 --> 12:27.063
The pressure system
coming in from the desert,

12:27.163 --> 12:28.481
it looks like we're not going
to get that.

12:28.581 --> 12:29.732
I've been telling you about that.

12:29.832 --> 12:32.631
Unfortunately,
that's not going to happen.

12:44.305 --> 12:45.522
"Ooms."

12:59.988 --> 13:01.014
Excuse me.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.661
$2.50 a night.

13:03.032 --> 13:05.911
Check-out 11:00 a.m. You pay in advance.

13:07.495 --> 13:08.897
May I see the room first?

13:08.997 --> 13:10.356
Yeah. Right behind me,
through those curtains.

13:10.456 --> 13:11.878
Take a look.

13:24.345 --> 13:26.456
It's rather crowded, isn't it?

13:26.556 --> 13:28.900
Yeah. We get good word-of-mouth.

13:32.895 --> 13:34.897
Do you have a single room?

13:36.899 --> 13:38.401
With or without a Jacuzzi?

13:40.111 --> 13:43.536
Look, I got one bed left.
You want it or not? Make up your mind.

13:44.032 --> 13:45.058
I'll take it.

13:45.158 --> 13:47.081
Here, sign the register.

13:53.833 --> 13:57.258
- What was that, a roach?
- No, a mouse. Just a baby.

13:57.545 --> 13:59.764
Look, that's $2.50 in advance.

14:01.257 --> 14:03.680
$2.50. $2.50.

14:04.552 --> 14:07.021
Could we have a private conversation?
Just entre nous?

14:09.432 --> 14:10.750
All right.

14:10.850 --> 14:13.920
Listen, I'm not really a derelict.
I'm down here on a wager.

14:14.020 --> 14:18.617
I happen to be one of the richest men
in the country, if not the richest.

14:19.192 --> 14:20.614
The richest?

14:20.860 --> 14:22.804
Yes. And if you give me a bed tonight,

14:22.904 --> 14:27.125
at the end of this month,
I will give you $10,000.

14:30.953 --> 14:33.547
All right. I'll up the ante.

14:34.123 --> 14:35.625
$20,000.

14:38.503 --> 14:41.177
Now you're talkin'. $20,000.

14:41.756 --> 14:43.850
Look, I'll give you a break.

14:44.509 --> 14:47.809
I don't need the whole $20,000 tonight.

14:48.471 --> 14:52.192
But if you give me
$2.50 as a down payment,

14:52.809 --> 14:54.127
the bed is yours.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.901
Otherwise, get the hell outta here!

16:00.501 --> 16:02.174
Who is it?

16:02.587 --> 16:04.214
Please let me in.

16:04.547 --> 16:05.948
I need shelter.

16:06.048 --> 16:10.394
I'm sorry. We're closed, my son.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.398
But I haven't eaten all day.

16:13.890 --> 16:15.312
I need food.

16:16.809 --> 16:20.188
We'll be open in the morning, my son.

16:21.731 --> 16:23.608
You don't understand.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.636
I don't have a place to sleep!

16:26.736 --> 16:29.472
I'm tired, very tired. Very.

16:29.572 --> 16:31.182
Please, please let me in.

16:31.282 --> 16:32.975
Please, let me in!

16:33.075 --> 16:35.144
Now, listen, you're waking everybody up!

16:35.244 --> 16:38.314
Now, you get outta here,
or I'll call the police!

16:38.414 --> 16:40.041
My son.

17:07.068 --> 17:08.694
Thank God.

17:42.895 --> 17:43.987
Hey!

17:44.689 --> 17:46.487
Jeez, you scared me!

17:46.983 --> 17:48.885
I didn't know anybody was under there!

17:48.985 --> 17:50.703
I always go here.

17:51.112 --> 17:52.739
I thought I saw someone,

17:52.947 --> 17:55.541
but then I thought it was
a frigment of my imagination.

17:55.783 --> 17:57.330
Why don't you look first?

17:57.994 --> 17:59.395
Yeah. You're right. You're right.

17:59.495 --> 18:01.213
Sorry.

18:02.373 --> 18:04.000
You almost hit me. That's disgusting!

18:05.293 --> 18:06.277
It is?

18:06.377 --> 18:07.424
Yes, it is!

18:07.795 --> 18:09.197
Why don't you use a handkerchief?

18:09.297 --> 18:11.324
Handkerchief?
I ain't got a handkerchief.

18:11.424 --> 18:12.926
I don't think I ever had a handkerchief.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.162
Here, take this.

18:16.262 --> 18:19.457
Gee, thanks.
Nobody down here ever gives you nothin'.

18:19.557 --> 18:21.184
You're all right.

18:26.022 --> 18:27.148
What are you doin'?

18:27.690 --> 18:31.069
P-E-P-T-O. Pepto!

18:31.444 --> 18:32.762
- What?
- It's hard to read backwards,

18:32.862 --> 18:34.580
but that's what it says. Pepto.

18:34.905 --> 18:38.034
You must have slept
on a Pepto-Bismol box.

18:38.242 --> 18:39.368
See?

18:40.328 --> 18:41.312
Yeah.

18:41.412 --> 18:44.211
Don't! Don't!
Don't rub it off. It's nice.

18:44.457 --> 18:45.942
That's a nice name, Pepto.

18:46.042 --> 18:47.443
I'm Sailor.

18:47.543 --> 18:50.387
Everybody calls me Sailor
'cause I was nearly in the Navy.

18:51.047 --> 18:52.532
Yeah, that's nice.

18:52.632 --> 18:55.260
Yeah, they wouldn't take me
'cause they said I had pleurilsy.

18:56.677 --> 18:58.204
Very nice meeting you.

18:58.304 --> 18:59.455
- Yeah.
- Yeah, well, goodbye.

18:59.555 --> 19:00.581
- Bye-bye. Nice to see you.
- Bye-bye.

19:00.681 --> 19:01.728
Bye.

19:03.684 --> 19:05.061
I just gave you a handkerchief.

19:06.228 --> 19:07.964
Yeah, but it's got initials.

19:08.064 --> 19:09.782
You can't blow snot in initials.

19:10.566 --> 19:12.568
- See you.
- Yeah. See you.

19:26.082 --> 19:27.483
Excuse me. I wonder...

19:27.583 --> 19:29.735
Could you tell me
where I could get something to eat?

19:29.835 --> 19:30.861
Don't ask me, pal.

19:30.961 --> 19:33.931
I don't know where
my next meal's comin' from.

19:48.771 --> 19:50.798
Get the hell outta here!

19:50.898 --> 19:53.968
I told all you goddamn bums,
I don't want you hanging around here.

19:54.068 --> 19:56.992
You gonna make it look like
a low-class place.

20:06.956 --> 20:08.378
Give to a poor blind man.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.636
Give to a poor blind man.

20:21.178 --> 20:24.352
Man, don't even think about it.

20:42.491 --> 20:43.663
Yeah!

20:58.507 --> 20:59.575
Good morning, sir.

20:59.675 --> 21:01.786
Hey, hey, hey, hey! Get away from my car!
What are you doing?

21:01.886 --> 21:03.245
I'm just cleaning your windshield, sir.

21:03.345 --> 21:06.189
Cleaning my windshield?
You made it worse!

21:07.600 --> 21:10.194
- There, that better?
- Wonderful.

21:11.020 --> 21:12.046
Can I have a dollar, please?

21:12.146 --> 21:14.215
Would you get away? Nothing's free!

21:14.315 --> 21:15.424
My hand!

21:15.524 --> 21:17.843
Wait! Wait! Wait, I'm caught!

21:17.943 --> 21:20.537
I'm caught. Wait, wait! Stop!

21:20.988 --> 21:22.661
Forget the dollar!

21:23.657 --> 21:25.601
Hot-too! Hot-too!
Ziggety beam bomb boom!

21:25.701 --> 21:26.953
Hot-too!

21:27.912 --> 21:29.730
Hot-too! Hot-too!
Ziggety beam bomb boom!

21:29.830 --> 21:31.047
Hot-too!

21:31.791 --> 21:33.651
Hot-too! Hot-too!
Ziggety beam bomb boom!

21:33.751 --> 21:35.003
Hot-too!

21:35.711 --> 21:37.655
Hot-too! Hot-too!
Ziggety beam bomb boom!

21:37.755 --> 21:39.007
Hot-too!

21:52.061 --> 21:53.358
A penny.

21:58.234 --> 22:00.136
Hot-too, hot-too!
Ziggety beam bomb boom!

22:00.236 --> 22:01.453
